fields.description:
Currently, there is no way to add dependencies to kick off dependent builds after the initial build of a newly created plan.

We should add an extra tab to allow users to assign plan dependencies while creating a plan, as this eliminates the additional step of editing plan to add a dependency.

From BSP-651
{quote}
when I create a new plane, cannot modify dependencies.

It's necessary for me, because new plane will be run after create and I will lost first run of dependency planes.{quote}

From http://forums.atlassian.com/thread.jspa?messageID=257276351#257276351

{quote}Just wondering - is there also a way to control the heartbeat time? It looks like the heartbeat pings the server every second or so. If this was a configurable option (to adjust it to every 2 minutes or 30 minutes, etc.) that would be great. I imagine I will have a lot of agents and this would just cut down on all the network chatter. I've poked around a bit in the admin pages and config files, and maybe it there, but I missed it.
{quote}
